review_blob: Agradezco a la cervecera Cuahtemoc por esta cerveza,  mas opciones es mejor, sin embargo en balance general queda debiendo, ahi esta el tostado y el aroma a cafe pero es demasiada ligera, muy poco cuerpo, sin embargo para una cerveza tan comercial es un buen intento. Prefiero las stout de Cucapa, Dos palomas y Minerva, cerveceras mas artesanales que empiezan a surgir.
Delicious strong ale, with a hint of fruit and brown sugar, just enough, in my opinion a must!
My first dopplebock, and I must say that now this is one of my favorite beers, tasty, malty, balanced alcoholic taste, lightly sweet and complex enough.
My first dopplebock, and I must say that now, this is one of my favorite beers, balanced alcoholic taste, malty, ligthly sweet and complex.
Nice beer, aroma like smoked jam, wood and spice, nothing that I ever tasted before, even so easily to drink and refreshing
Maybe the best stout in my town, dark head, malty, strong coffe and chocolate flavors, need another one
